12 SUMMARY
1133 Current law provides that the District Court may revoke the certificate of a code
1144 enforcement officer under certain circumstances. This bill eliminates that provision and
1155 provides that complaints regarding code enforcement officers may be filed with the
1166 Director of the Maine Office of Community Affairs. The bill establishes a complaint
1177 review committee whose members are appointed by the director. The director may refer
1188 complaints to the complaint review committee. The complaint review committee must
1199 investigate these complaints and recommend appropriate action to the director. The bill
2200 authorizes the director to impose various forms of discipline upon a certificate holder or an
2211 applicant for a certificate.
